article.headline: Saint Mary's 69, Portland 55
article.story: LAS VEGAS -- Omar Samhan had 16 points and 13 rebounds, Mickey McConnell scored 16 points and Saint Mary's advanced to the West Coast Conference tournament final for the second straight year with a 69-55 victory over Portland on Sunday night. Matthew Dellavedova also had 16 points for the second-seeded Gaels (25-5), who will face No. 18 Gonzaga on Monday night at the Orleans Arena. The Zags routed Saint Mary's 83-58 in last season's final. Jorden Page scored 14 points as the Gaels pulled away with a 27-8 run in the second half. Ethan Niedermeyer scored 12 points for the third-seeded Pilots (21-10), who made less than 29 percent of their shots. Leading scorer T.J. Campbell managed just seven points on 2-for-12 shooting, and Robin Smeulders was 3 for 12.
